The Independent Policing Oversight Authority is investigating claims that an AP officer attached to Kegonga police division, Kuria East, shot and killed a man over a game of billiards, locally known as ajua. Ipoa head of communication Denis Oketch yesterday said the agency is looking “into the incident to unravel the circumstance that led to fatal shooting.” Witnesses said the officer trailed and shot dead the man at Kegonga market on Monday at 10am. Residents said on Friday the officer had disagreement with the man over ajua. On Monday, Kuria East police boss Ahmed Abdikadir denied the claims. He said the deceased was a known robber. He said he was shot by the officer after he resisted arrest and attempted to grab the cop’s firearm.